533 LIEBFRAUMLICH 1962 (Baumer) Although Liebfraumilch represents the lowest common denominator, it is far and away the most popular label. Here is not great wine but pleasant, suitable Liebfrau- milch at wonderfully low cost.

557 NIERSTEINER SCHNAFFENBERG 1962 The softness of the Rheinhessia is apparent here. Pleas- ing —a typical and good Niersteiner.

537 RUDESHEIMER 1962 (Baumer) Produced high in the hillsides overlooking the colorful town of Rudesheim. Worth at least 50% more.

577 ST. JOHANNER GEIERSBERG 1961 Estate bottled in a small vineyard not far from Bingen. Soft, good character, dry.

553 BERNCASTLER BRAUNES 1962

Light, dry, truly delicate and eminently satisfying.

547 PIESPORTER MICHELSBERG 1962

A regional delicate dry Moselle from a renowned wine growing township.

594 MONZELER KATZCHEN 1961

Not well known in America but much appreciated by the local Moselle inhabitants. Estate bottled. Worth twice the price.

629 PIESPORTER GOLDTROPFCHEN 1962 You should quickly get this one. The price is sensational. It was offered last month at $2.49. The label bears the portrait of William Shakespeare. Rhenish is a white wine of which the Bard spoke fondly.
